---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { games, gearPicks } from '../../data/games';
export function getStaticPaths(){return games.map(game=>({params:{slug:game.slug},props:{game}}));}
const { game } = Astro.props;
const platform = Astro.url.pathname.includes('rog-ally') ? 'ROG Ally' : 'Steam Deck';
const fps = platform === 'ROG Ally' ? game.allyFps : game.deckFps;
const canonical = `https://handheldsettings.com/${platform === 'ROG Ally' ? 'rog-ally-settings' : 'steam-deck-settings'}/${game.slug}/`;
const jsonLd = [
  {'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'TechArticle',headline:`${game.title} ${platform} settings`,description:`Baseline ${platform} settings for ${game.title}: ${fps}, storage, battery, and tuning guidance.`,image:`https://handheldsettings.com${game.image}`,dateModified:'2026-07-21',mainEntityOfPage:canonical,author:{'@type':'Organization',name:'Handheld Settings Lab'}},
  {'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'BreadcrumbList',itemListElement:[
    {'@type':'ListItem',position:1,name:'Home',item:'https://handheldsettings.com/'},
    {'@type':'ListItem',position:2,name:`${platform} settings`,item:`https://handheldsettings.com/${platform === 'ROG Ally' ? 'rog-ally-settings' : 'steam-deck-settings'}/`},
    {'@type':'ListItem',position:3,name:game.title,item:canonical}
  ]},
  {'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'FAQPage',mainEntity:[
    {'@type':'Question',name:`What FPS target should I use for ${game.title} on ${platform}?`,acceptedAnswer:{'@type':'Answer',text:`Our baseline target is ${fps}. It is a starting point rather than a guaranteed benchmark; patches, device settings, thermals, and game areas can change performance.`}},
    {'@type':'Question',name:`How much storage does ${game.title} need?`,acceptedAnswer:{'@type':'Answer',text:`Plan for about ${game.storage}GB plus extra free space for updates, shader caches, saves, and launcher overhead.`}},
    {'@type':'Question',name:`How can I improve battery life in ${game.title}?`,acceptedAnswer:{'@type':'Answer',text:'Use a stable frame cap, reduce screen brightness, lower the device power target when practical, and lower expensive effects before sacrificing texture clarity.'}}
  ]}
];
---
<Base title={`${game.title} ${platform} settings: FPS, battery and storage — Handheld Settings Lab`} description={`Best baseline ${platform} settings for ${game.title}: target ${fps}, ${game.storage}GB storage estimate, battery guidance, frame pacing, and tuning checklist.`} image={game.image} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
<article class="wrap article"><span class="eyebrow">{platform} settings guide · Updated July 2026</span><h1>{game.title} {platform} settings</h1><p class="lede muted">A practical starting point for {game.title} on {platform}. These are baseline tuning notes; we update pages as patch notes, public specs, and credible performance reports change.</p><figure class="game-hero"><img src={game.image} alt={game.imageAlt}/><figcaption class="media-credit">Editorial game image: {game.imageSource}. Source: <a href={game.sourceUrl} rel="nofollow">Steam store page</a>. Trademarks and artwork belong to their owners.</figcaption></figure><div class="settings-panel"><div class="card"><h3>Target</h3><div class="stat">{fps}</div></div><div class="card"><h3>Preset</h3><p>{game.preset}</p></div><div class="card"><h3>Battery planning</h3><p>{game.battery}</p></div><div class="card"><h3>Install size</h3><div class="stat">{game.storage}GB</div></div></div><h2>Recommended baseline</h2><p>{game.notes}</p><p>Start from the game’s low or medium preset and make one change at a time. A stable cap generally feels better on a handheld screen than a higher average with uneven frame pacing. Keep enough free storage for updates and shader-cache growth; nearly full drives can make patching and troubleshooting harder.</p><h2>What to change first</h2><ol><li><strong>Set the frame cap.</strong> Choose the target above before chasing higher graphics settings.</li><li><strong>Lower shadows, volumetrics, and crowd density.</strong> These often cost more performance than texture quality.</li><li><strong>Use upscaling carefully.</strong> Start with a quality mode, then move toward balanced only if the cap is unstable.</li><li><strong>Tune power after the game is stable.</strong> Reduce TDP/power gradually while watching frame pacing.</li><li><strong>Test demanding areas.</strong> Menus and opening scenes are not representative of the whole game.</li></ol><div class="callout"><strong>Lab note:</strong> We do not invent benchmark numbers. This page is a source/spec/community-informed baseline until direct test notes are explicitly documented.</div><h2>Battery and storage planning</h2><p>The battery range above is a planning estimate, not a manufacturer promise. Brightness, refresh rate, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth accessories, battery health, power profile, and game updates can all change runtime. For storage, reserve additional space beyond the listed install size so patches do not force emergency deletions.</p><p><a class="btn" href="/calculators/storage-planner/">Check storage</a> <a class="btn ghost" href="/calculators/battery-estimator/">Estimate battery</a></p><h2>Useful handheld gear</h2><p class="affiliate-note">Disclosure: shopping links are marked sponsored. We only claim hands-on testing when a page explicitly documents it. Otherwise these are spec-based product/search shortlists.</p><div class="grid cols2">{gearPicks.slice(0,2).map(item => <div class="card gear-card"><span class="chip">{item.bestFor}</span><h3>{item.title}</h3><p class="muted">{item.verdict}</p><a class="btn ghost" href={item.amazonUrl} rel="nofollow sponsored" target="_blank" data-affiliate-link data-category="game-settings">Compare on Amazon</a></div>)}</div><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><h3>What FPS target should I use?</h3><p>Start with {fps}. If demanding areas repeatedly fall below the cap, lower expensive settings or choose the next lower stable target rather than accepting constant swings.</p><h3>How much free storage should I keep?</h3><p>Plan for the listed {game.storage}GB install plus room for updates, shader caches, saves, screenshots, and temporary patch files.</p><h3>What improves battery life first?</h3><p>Use a stable cap, lower brightness, reduce the device power target when practical, and cut expensive effects before making the whole image blurry.</p></article>
</Base>
